Oct 26 1872
Mrs A J Kendall
Dear Madam
When I left my home in Conn(ecticut?
I expected with great certainty to deliver the enclosed
package in person. I told your good unclear I would do
so, but I was compelled by uncontrolable circumstances
to deny myself the pleasure of visiting your city
and delivering the package. and now I must do 
the next best thing - forward it by mail
Respectfully yours
Mrs Dibble
